message.content:
We factor the quadratic to get $(a-3)(a-7) \le 0$. We make a sign table.
\begin{tabular}{c|ccc|c} &$a-3$ &$a-7$ &&$(a-3)(a-7)$ \\ \hline$a<3$ &$-$&$-$&$+$&$+$\\ [.1cm]$3<a<7$ &$+$&$-$&$-$&$+$\\ [.1cm]$a>7$ &$+$&$+$&$+$&$+$\\ [.1cm]\end{tabular}The values of $a$ that work are $3 \le a \le 7$, so the greatest value of $a$ is $\boxed{7}$.
